<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n03113b"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n03" href="#n03113b">N03 (VI.B.3)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n03all.htm#n03113b"> 113(b)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> on short commons</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">In a furnished room, other people do not know it when you go hungry. &hellip; On Sunday mornings she feasted royally on veal chops and pineapple fritters at &ldquo;Billy&apos;s&rdquo; restaurant, at a cost of twenty-five cents &hellip; She had her lunches in the department-store restaurant at a cost of sixty cents for the week; dinners were $1.05. <small> O. Henry, <a name="OHFM" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#OHFM"><cite title="source">The Four Million</cite></a> (1906) [&lsquo;An Unfinished Story&rdquo;] 178</small></blockquote> <mm class="note">Note: The phrase &lsquo;to go <i>on short commons</i>&rsquo; means to have insufficient to eat. </mm> </dd></dl>
